chel%20Berlin%20Benjamin%20is%20a%20partner%20at%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbeal.law%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeal%20Sutherland%20Berlin%20%26amp%3B%20Brown.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe's%20helped%20pregnant%20people%20navigate%20discrimination%20laws.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20recommends%20people%20contact%20a%20lawyer%20if%20they%20suspect%20they%20are%20being%20discriminated.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Rachel%20Berlin%20Benjamin.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%E2%80%99m%20a%20plaintiff%E2%80%99s%20employment%20attorney%2C%20or%20someone%20who%20specializes%20in%20workers%E2%80%99%20rights.%20I%20help%20employees%20who%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubtle-ways-women-treated-differently-work-2014-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediscriminated%20against%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20pursuing%20claims%20of%20discrimination%20or%20retaliation%20and%20receiving%20the%20payments%20they%20may%20be%20entitled%20to%20if%20they%20have%20legal%20claims.%20I%E2%80%99ve%20helped%20people%20across%20all%20industries%20and%20jobs%20who%20have%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-your-boss-can-legally-do-2016-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunlawful%20discrimination%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20retaliation%2C%20or%20sexual%20harassment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20victim%20advocate%20and%20a%20mom%20of%20two%2C%20I%E2%80%99ve%20been%20able%20to%20help%20dozens%20of%20pregnant%20people%20who%20have%20been%20unfairly%20treated%20in%20the%20workplace.%20As%20many%20industries%20undergo%20layoffs%2C%20here%20are%20some%20things%20to%20keep%20in%20mind.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you%E2%80%99re%20fired%20after%20getting%20pregnant%20or%20taking%20maternity%20leave%2C%20you%20might%20be%20the%20victim%20of%20discrimination%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20of%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcan-you-legally-get-fired-while-on-maternity-or-paternity-leave-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elet%20go%20while%20pregnant%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20shortly%20after%20giving%20birth%20is%20surely%20an%20emotional%20and%20stressful%20time%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20know%20your%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPregnancy%20alone%20cannot%20be%20grounds%20for%20termination.%20If%20an%20employer%20demotes%2C%20fires%2C%20fails%20to%20accommodate%2C%20or%20mistreats%20someone%20solely%20because%20they%20are%20pregnant%2C%20then%20that%20likely%20violates%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fpregnancy-discrimination-act%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPregnancy%20Discrimination%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeoc.gov%2Fstatutes%2Ftitle-vii-civil-rights-act-1964%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTitle%2520VII%2520prohibits%2520employment%2520discrimination%2Cseveral%2520sections%2520of%2520Title%2520VII.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETitle%20VII%20of%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20or%20the%20newly%20enacted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeoc.gov%2Fstatutes%2Fpregnant-workers-fairness-act%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520PWFA%252C%2520which%2520is%2520administered%2Cthe%2520employer%2520an%2520undue%2520hardship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPregnant%20Workers%20Fairness%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20important%20federal%20laws%20help%20protect%20women%20and%20pregnant%20employees%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20but%20they%20will%20only%20apply%20if%20the%20employer%20has%20at%20least%2015%20employees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETitle%20VII%20and%20the%20Pregnancy%20Discrimination%20Act%20prohibit%20sex%20discrimination%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20pregnancy.%20In%202023%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eeoc.gov%2Fwysk%2Fwhat-you-should-know-about-pregnant-workers-fairness-act%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPregnant%20Workers%20Fairness%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20into%20effect%20and%20made%20clear%20that%20employers%20need%20to%20provide%20reasonable%20accommodations%20to%20an%20employee%E2%80%99s%20known%20limitations%20related%20to%20pregnancy%2C%20childbirth%2C%20or%20related%20medical%20conditions.%20This%20could%20include%20changes%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20job%2C%20workplace%20and%20schedule%2C%20and%20requests%20for%20light-duty%20work%20or%20job%20modifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20circumstances%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-walkout-organizers-say-company-retaliated-against-them-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20person%20is%20demoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20let%20go%20for%20non-discriminatory%20reasons%20unrelated%20to%20the%20worker%E2%80%99s%20pregnancy.%20Employers%20could%20decide%20to%20discipline%20or%20terminate%20a%20pregnant%20worker%20because%20of%20legitimate%20performance%20issues%2C%20personality%20differences%2C%20or%20a%20reduction%20in%20workforce%2C%20for%20example.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiscrimination%20can%20also%20happen%20during%20parental%20leave%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fagencies%2Fwhd%2Ffmla%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFamily%20and%20Medical%20Leave%20Act%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(FMLA)%20is%20a%20federal%20law%20that%20allows%20employees%20who%20have%20been%20working%20for%20a%20company%20for%20at%20least%20a%20year%20full-time%20to%20take%2012%20weeks%20of%20unpaid%20leave.%20That%20could%20be%20for%20a%20serious%20medical%20condition%2C%20taking%20care%20of%20a%20sick%20family%20member%2C%20or%20giving%20birth.%20FMLA%20is%20not%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmaternity-leave-around-the-world-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20parental%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20FMLA%20generally%20offers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-far-behind-the-us-is-in-offering-worker-protections-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20employees%2C%20it%20does%20not%20make%20an%20employee%20%E2%80%9Ctermination%20proof.%E2%80%9D%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20be%20legally%20fired%20during%20FMLA%20leave%20if%20the%20employer%20can%20show%20the%20employee%20was%20terminated%20for%20reasons%20completely%20unrelated%20to%20FMLA%20leave%2C%20or%20the%20decision%20to%20terminate%20the%20worker%20is%20documented%20and%20decided%20before%20the%20worker%20contemplates%20FMLA%20leave%2C%20for%20example.%20However%2C%20it%20raises%20a%20red%20flag%20if%20I%20see%20someone%20being%20fired%20during%20FMLA%20leave%20or%20shortly%20after%20they%20return%20from%20the%20leave.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20wait%20until%20you%20are%20terminated%20to%20contact%20a%20lawyer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20get%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fto-do-after-get-laid-off-how-make-best-it-2020-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseverance%20package%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20you%E2%80%99re%20let%20go%20while%20pregnant%20or%20on%20leave%2C%20and%20there%20might%20be%20language%20in%20there%20saying%20to%20contact%20a%20lawyer.%20That%E2%80%99s%20usually%20when%20people%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20to%20take%20that%20step.%20But%20if%20you%20feel%20like%20you%E2%80%99ve%20been%20targeted%20because%20of%20pregnancy%20or%20medical%20leave%20at%20any%20time%20during%20employment%2C%20you%20should%20contact%20a%20plaintiff%E2%80%99s%20employment%20lawyer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20you%20contact%20a%20lawyer%20who%20specializes%20in%20this%20area%2C%20the%20better%20because%20we%20can%20help%20you%20navigate%20a%20lot%3A%20what%20to%20document%2C%20whether%20to%20record%20conversations%2C%20how%20to%20respond%20to%20employer%20emails%20or%20texts%2C%20what%20to%20say%2C%20and%20how%20to%20protect%20yourself.%20We%20will%20also%20help%20you%20get%20a%20better%20understanding%20of%20the%20deadlines%20that%20exist%20to%20pursue%20these%20types%20of%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEmployment%20lawyer%20fees%20vary%20for%20discrimination%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20legal%20consultation%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20have%20to%20be%20paid.%20A%20lot%20of%20times%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20legal%20claim%20under%20any%20of%20the%20statutes%2C%20your%20consultation%20might%20be%20free%20because%20your%20claims%20are%20valuable.%20Lawyers%20in%20this%20field%20work%20both%20on%20a%20contingency%20fee%20(taking%20a%20percentage%20of%20your%20settlement)%20or%20based%20on%20their%20hourly%20rates.%20If%20you%20feel%20you%20need%20a%20lawyer%2C%20call%20a%20firm%20specializing%20in%20representing%20employees%20and%20tell%20them%20what%20is%20going%20on.%20You%20don%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20need%20documents%2C%20recordings%2C%20or%20video%20to%20prove%20your%20case.%20Your%20word%20is%20good%20enough.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompensation%20for%20discrimination%20can%20vary.%20Under%20employment%20discrimination%20laws%2C%20lost%20wages%20can%20be%20recovered%20until%20you%20find%20new%20work%2C%20potentially%20including%20differences%20to%20your%20previous%20salary%20and%20%26quot%3Bfront%20pay%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20future.%20However%2C%20recovering%20these%20damages%20requires%20diligently%20seeking%20new%20jobs%20and%20documenting%20your%20efforts%20to%20minimize%20losses.%20Compensatory%20damages%20are%20also%20available%20but%20capped%20based%20on%20your%20employer's%20size.%20Every%20case%20is%20different.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20