versy%20after%20the%20Returning%20Officer%2C%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20was%20caught%20on%20camera%20deliberately%20invalidating%20and%20discarding%20eight%20votes%20in%20his%20favour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Masih%20also%20faces%20a%20contempt%20of%20court%20action%20-%20he%20has%20been%20issued%20a%20'show%20cause'%20notice%20-%20that%20has%20been%20initiated%20by%20the%20top%20court%2C%20which%20came%20down%20strongly%20on%20the%20former%20BJP%20Minority%20Cell%20member%2C%20who%20was%20repeatedly%20warned%20of%20prosecution%20if%20he%20was%20found%20to%20have%20lied%20to%20the%20court%20in%20any%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShould%20Mr%20Masih%20be%20prosecuted%20-%20in%20an%20earlier%20hearing%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20called%20his%20actions%20a%20%26quot%3Bmockery%20of%20democracy%26quot%3B%20and%20indicated%20it%20would%20do%20just%20that%20-%20it%20will%20be%20a%20historic%20first%20in%20independent%20India%2C%20and%20a%20stern%20warning%20to%20potential%20hijacking%20of%20poll%20results%20weeks%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20landmark%20judgement%20also%20means%20the%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress%20-%20which%20contested%20the%20election%20in%20alliance%20with%20each%20other%20-%20have%20recorded%20the%20INDIA%20bloc's%20first%20win%20as%20it%20bids%20to%20defeat%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20much%20as%20the%20court's%20order%20will%20be%20welcomed%20by%20the%20AAP%20and%20Kuldeep%20Kumar%2C%20it%20will%20also%20be%20a%20shot%20in%20the%20arm%20for%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20which%20is%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20breaking%20up%2C%20less%20than%20a%20year%20after%20it%20was%20formed%2C%20amid%20disagreements%20between%20members%20on%20seat-sharing%20and%20poll%20prep%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20today%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20examined%20the%20eight%20discarded%20ballot%20papers.%20Mr%20Masih%20had%20on%20Monday%20told%20the%20court%20he%20had%20marked%20these%20eight%20because%20they%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bdefaced%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20councillors%20themselves%2C%20and%20he%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20the%20votes%20were%20not%20counted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20law%2C%20double-marked%20ballot%20papers%2C%20or%20those%20with%20marks%20that%20identify%20the%20lawmaker%2C%20or%20are%20marked%20in%20any%20other%20way%2C%20are%20considered%20%26quot%3Binvalid%26quot%3B%20and%20cannot%20be%20included%20in%20the%20counting%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20began%20today's%20hearing%20by%20asking%20Mr%20Masih%20to%20point%20out%20how%20the%20ballots%20were%20%26quot%3Bdefaced%26quot%3B.%20Appearing%20for%20the%20Returning%20Officer%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Mukul%20Rohatgi%2C%20pointed%20to%20small%20dots%20and%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3B...%20(so)%20he%20assessed%20certain%20ballots%20were%20invalid.%20He%20is%20not%20a%20thief...%20it%20was%20his%20assessment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20was%20distinctly%20unconvinced%2C%20and%20noted%20%26quot%3BAll%20eight%20have%20received%20the%20stamp%20for%20Kuldeep%20Kumar...%20the%20votes%20are%20cast%20for%20Mr%20Kumar.%20What%20he%20(Mr%20Masih)%20does%20is...%20he%20puts%20a%20single%20line...%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EControversy%20over%20the%20results%20of%20the%20Chandigarh%20mayoral%20race%20broke%20after%20a%20video%20of%20the%20counting%20process%20was%20widely%20shared%20online.%20The%20video%20showed%20Mr%20Masih%20surreptitiously%20marking%20some%20ballot%20papers.%20Halfway%20through%20his%20act%20he%20glances%20up%20and%20realises%20his%20actions%20are%20being%20recorded%20by%20CCTVs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20video%20triggered%20furious%20protests%20by%20the%20AAP%20and%20the%20Congress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%20Mayoral%20Election%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP's%20Manoj%20Sonkar%20was%20declared%20the%20winner%20after%20the%20contentious%20counting%20of%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolling%20officials%20gave%20Mr%20Sonkar%2016%20votes%20to%20Mr%20Kumar's%2012%3B%20had%20the%20eight%20votes%20been%20counted%2C%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20directed%2C%20the%20AAP%20candidate%20would%20have%20recorded%20a%20comfortable%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%20three%20AAP%20councillors%20have%20sided%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20significantly%20changing%20the%20equation%20in%20this%20election.%20The%20BJP%20now%20has%2019%20votes%20in%20the%2035-member%20house%2C%20including%20that%20of%20the%20Chandigarh%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20who%20has%20voting%20rights%20as%20an%20ex-officio%20member.%20The%20AAP-Congress%20have%20only%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20court%20had%20ordered%20a%20re-election%20-%20as%20was%20sought%20by%20Mr%20Sonkar%20-%20the%20BJP%20would%20have%20had%20a%20clear%20advantage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENDTV%20is%20now%20available%20on%20WhatsApp%20channels.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whatsapp.com%2Fchannel%2F0029Va4lixw7z4kcvZI9JM12%5C%22%3EClick%20on%20the%20link%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20get%20all%20the%20latest%20updates%20from%20NDTV%20on%20your%20chat.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708428360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fd3dn3jfg_anil-masih_625x300_20_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faap-candidate-kuldeep-kumar-to-be-chandigarh-mayor-supreme-court-5093458%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Tuesday%20ruled%20Kuldeep%20Kumar%20the%20lawful%20winner%20of%20last%20month's%20Chandigarh%20mayoral%20election%2C%20ending%20weeks%20of%20controversy%20fuelled%20by%20the%20Returning%20Officer%2C%20Anil%20Masih%2C%20deliberately%20invalidating%20eight%20votes%20for%20the%20AAP%20leader.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faap-candidate-kuldeep-kumar-to-be-chandigarh-mayor-supreme-court-5093458%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faap-candidate-kuldeep-kumar-to-be-chandigarh-mayor-supreme-court-5093458%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Faap-candidate-kuldeep-kumar-to-be-chandigarh-mayor-supreme-court-5093458%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Right%20To%20Adopt%20Child%20Can't%20Be%20Fundamental%20Right%2C%20Declares%20Delhi%20High%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20to%20adopt%20a%20child%20cannot%20be%20raised%20to%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20the%20prospective%20adoptive%20parents%20do%20not%20have%20any%20right%20to%20choose%20who%20to%20adopt%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Subramonium%20Prasad%20upheld%20the%20retrospective%20application%20of%20a%20regulation%20permitting%20couples%20with%20two%20or%20more%20children%20to%20only%20adopt%20children%20with%20special%20needs%20or%20those%20hard%20to%20place%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20process%20operates%20for%20the%20welfare%20of%20children%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20prospective%20adoptive%20parents%20(PAPs)%20cannot%20be%20put%20at%20the%20forefront.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20right%20to%20adopt%20cannot%20be%20raised%20to%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right%20within%20Article%2021%20nor%20can%20it%20be%20raised%20to%20a%20level%20granting%20PAPs%20the%20right%20to%20demand%20their%20choice%20of%20who%20to%20adopt.%20The%20adoption%20process%20in%20entirety%20operates%20on%20the%20premise%20of%20welfare%20of%20children%20and%20therefore%20the%20rights%20flowing%20within%20the%20adoption%20framework%20does%20not%20place%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20PAPs%20at%20the%20forefront%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20court%20in%20a%20recent%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20noted%20that%20there%20is%20a%20long%20wait%20for%20adoption%20and%20there%20are%20many%20childless%20couples%20and%20parents%20with%20one%20child%20who%20would%20adopt%20a%20%26quot%3Bnormal%20child%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20chances%20of%20a%20specially-abled%20child%20being%20adopted%20are%20remote%20and%20the%20regulation%20therefore%20only%20aims%20to%20ensure%20that%20more%20and%20more%20children%20with%20special%20needs%20get%20adopted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20long%20wait%20for%20prospective%20parents%20including%20those%20who%20are%20devoid%20of%20even%20one%20biological%20child%20must%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20backdrop%20of%20a%20grave%20mismatch%20between%20the%20number%20of%20normal%20children%20available%20for%20adoption%20and%20the%20number%20of%20PAPs%20in%20expectation%20of%20adopting%20a%20normal%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20balanced%20approach%20therefore%20ought%20to%20be%20welcomed%20which%20attempts%20to%20reduce%20the%20wait%20for%20parents%20with%20a%20single%20child%20or%20devoid%20of%20even%20that%2C%20in%20anticipation%20of%20adoption%20and%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20child%20while%20being%20matched%20with%20a%20family%20with%20lesser%20number%20of%20already%20existing%20biological%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court's%20decision%20came%20on%20a%20batch%20of%20petitions%20by%20several%20PAPs%20with%20two%20biological%20children%20who%20applied%20for%20adoption%20of%20a%20third%20child%20as%20per%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20(Care%20and%20Protection%20of%20Children)%20Act%2C%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pendency%20of%20their%20application%2C%20the%20Adoption%20Rules%2C%202022%20superseded%20the%20Adoption%20Regulations%2C%202017%20and%20instead%20of%20three%20or%20more%20children%2C%20now%20couples%20with%20two%20or%20more%20children%20could%20only%20opt%20for%20adoption%20of%20children%20with%20special%20needs%20or%20those%20hard%20to%20place%20children%20unless%20they%20are%20relatives%20or%20step-children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHard%20to%20place%20children%20are%20those%20that%20are%20not%20likely%20to%20be%20adopted%20because%20of%20physical%20or%20mental%20disability%2C%20emotional%20disturbance%2C%20recognised%20high%20risk%20of%20physical%20or%20mental%20disease%2C%20age%2C%20racial%20or%20ethnic%20factors%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20contended%20that%20retrospective%20application%20of%20the%20Adoption%20Regulations%202022%20was%20arbitrary%20and%20violative%20of%20Article%2014%20(equality%20before%20law)%20of%20the%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20order%20dismissing%20the%20petitions%2C%20the%20court%20said%20there%20was%20%26quot%3Bno%20right%20at%20all%26quot%3B%20to%20insist%20on%20the%20adoption%20of%20a%20particular%20child%20and%20the%20petitioners'%20claim%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Bvested%20right%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20retrospectively%20taken%20away%20was%20not%20good%20in%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20policy%20of%20the%20legislature%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20that%20the%20rush%20of%20a%20number%20of%20couples%2C%20who%20already%20have%20more%20than%20four%20children%2C%20who%20are%20available%20to%20adopt%20a%20child%20was%20felt%20in%20the%20year%202015.%20The%20said%20figure%20of%20four%20was%20brought%20down%20to%20three%20in%20the%20year%202017%20and%20the%20same%20has%20now%20been%20brought%20down%20to%20two%20in%20the%20year%202022.%20This%20indicates%20that%20there%20is%20no%20right%20amongst%20the%20PAPs%20to%20insist%20on%20the%20child%20whom%20they%20want%20to%20adopt%20till%20the%20adoption%20does%20not%20go%20through.%20The%20change%20is%20only%20in%20the%20eligibility%20criteria%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20the%20registration%20of%20the%20petitioners%20as%20PAPs%20was%20still%20intact%20and%20they%20were%20within%20the%20zone%20of%20consideration%20towards%20adoption%20of%20a%20special%20needs%20child%2C%20hard%20to%20place%20children%20and%20children%20of%20relatives%20or%20step%20children.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708428180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2016-12%2Fmoher-child-generic-istock_650x400_81482695118.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fright-to-adopt-child-cant-be-fundamental-right-declares-delhi-high-court-5093248%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20right%20to%20adopt%20a%20child%20cannot%20be%20raised%20to%20the%20status%20of%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20the%20prospective%20adoptive%20parents%20do%20not%20have%20any%20right%20to%20choose%20who%20to%20adopt%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fright-to-adopt-child-cant-be-fundamental-right-declares-delhi-high-court-5093248%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fright-to-adopt-child-cant-be-fundamental-right-declares-delhi-high-court-5093248%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fright-to-adopt-child-cant-be-fundamental-right-declares-delhi-high-court-5093248%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chandigarh%20Mayor%20Polls%20Returning%20Officer%20Served%20Notice%20By%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20returning%20officer%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20Chandigarh%20vote-tampering%20row%20is%20guilty%20of%20misdemeanour%20and%20made%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20deface%20eight%20ballot%20papers%20so%20that%20BJP's%20candidate%20is%20elected%20the%20city's%20mayor%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20held%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20has%20now%20directed%20contempt%20of%20court%20proceedings%20against%20the%20officer%2C%20Anil%20Masih.%20A%20showcause%20notice%20has%20been%20issued%2C%20and%20he%20has%20been%20asked%20to%20file%20a%20response%20in%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20High%20Court%20within%20three%20weeks.%20The%20returning%20officer%20was%20earlier%20removed%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20BJP's%20minority%20cell%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20massive%20row%20over%20a%20video%20of%20him%20tampering%20with%20the%20ballot%20papers%20after%20the%20January%2030%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20noted%20that%20all%20the%20eight%20ballot%20papers%20declared%20invalid%20by%20returning%20officer%20Anil%20Masih%20were%20in%20the%20favour%20of%20AAP%20candidate%20and%20petitioner%20Kuldeep%20Kumar.%20The%20court%20has%20now%20ordered%20that%20Mr%20Kumar%20will%20now%20take%20over%20as%20Chandigarh%20mayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Presiding%20Officer%20is%20guilty%20of%20misdemeanour.%20It%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20Presiding%20Officer%20has%20made%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20deface%20eight%20ballots%20which%20were%20cast%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20petitioner%20so%20that%20the%20eighth%20respondent%20will%20be%20declared%20as%20the%20elected%20candidate%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Masih's%20conduct%2C%20the%20court%20said%2C%20has%20to%20be%20deprecated%20at%20two%20levels.%20%26quot%3BFirstly%2C%20he%20has%20unlawfully%20altered%20the%20course%20of%20Mayoral%20election.%20Secondly%2C%20in%20making%20a%20solemn%20statement%20before%20this%20Court%20on%2019%20February%2C%20the%20Presiding%20Officer%20expressed%20falsehood%20for%20which%20he%20must%20be%20held%20accountable%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court's%20ruling%20against%20the%20poll%20officer%20came%20after%20strong%20observations%20on%20the%20viral%20video%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20hearing.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20had%20earlier%20termed%20his%20act%20a%20%26quot%3Bmockery%20of%20democracy%26quot%3B.%20The%20officer%20was%20yesterday%20grilled%20in%20the%20court%20on%20why%20he%20was%20putting%20an%20%26quot%3Bx%26quot%3B%20mark%20on%20the%20ballot%20papers.%20He%20replied%20that%20the%20ballot%20papers%20had%20been%20defaced%20and%20he%20was%20marking%20them%20so%20that%20they%20could%20be%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20morning%2C%20the%20video%20was%20replayed%20in%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20bench%20held%20that%20the%20ballot%20papers%20were%20not%20defaced.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Masih%20had%20declared%20as%20invalid%20eight%20votes%20in%20support%20of%20the%20AAP%20mayoral%20candidate.%20This%20ensured%20the%20victory%20of%20the%20BJP%20nominee%2C%20even%20though%20the%20party%20had%20lesser%20votes%20than%20the%20AAP-Congress%20combine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court's%20order%20also%20puts%20an%20end%20to%20speculation%20that%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20recently%20engineered%20a%20switchover%20by%203%20AAP%20councillors%2C%20may%20eventually%20manage%20to%20hold%20on%20the%20Chandigarh%20civic%20body.%20The%20switchover%20meant%20that%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20re-election%2C%20the%20BJP%20would%20score%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20AAP-Congress%20alliance.%20The%20court%2C%20however%2C%20declined%20to%20order%20a%20reelection%20after%20noting%20that%20horsetrading%20is%20a%20serious%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708428060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F9pgcd15g_anil-masih_625x300_20_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fchandigarh-mayor-polls-returning-officer-served-notice-by-supreme-court-5093582%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20returning%20officer%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20Chandigarh%20vote-tampering%20row%20is%20guilty%20of%20misdemeanour%20and%20made%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20deface%20eight%20ballot%20papers%20so%20that%20BJP's%20candidate%20is%20elected%20the%20city's%20mayor%2C%20t