0customer-service%20bot.%20Thirty%20seconds%20after%20the%20call%20ended%2C%20Pietsch%20later%20reported%2C%20the%20company%20cut%20off%20her%20access%20to%20her%20corporate%20laptop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20must%20be%20very%20easy%20for%20you%20to%20just%20have%20these%20little%2010-minute%2C%2015-minute%20meetings%2C%20tell%20someone%20that%20they're%20fired%2C%20completely%20wreck%20their%20whole%20life%2C%20and%20then%20that's%20it%20with%20no%20explanation%2C%26quot%3B%20Pietsch%20tells%20the%20two%20Cloudflare%20representatives%20on%20the%20call.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20let%20go%20for%20no%20reason%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20a%20huge%20slap%20in%20the%20face%20from%20a%20company%20that%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20believe%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObservers%20have%20since%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2024%2F01%2F12%2Fcloudflare-employee-firing-tiktok-layoff-disguise%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edebated%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20whether%20Pietsch's%20termination%20was%20really%20a%20layoff%20dressed%20up%20as%20a%20firing%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20trick%20employers%20sometimes%20pull%20to%20avoid%20paying%20severance.%20But%20regardless%20of%20her%20specific%20circumstances%2C%20I%20think%20the%20video%20struck%20a%20chord%20because%20it%20conveys%20how%20it%20%3Cem%3Efeels%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20viscerally%2C%20to%20be%20let%20go%20by%20the%20cold%20and%20heartless%20machinery%20employed%20by%20so%20many%20companies%20today.%20One%20week%2C%20your%20bosses%20are%20crowing%20about%20how%20the%20company%20is%20one%20big%20family.%20The%20next%20week%2C%20they%20deploy%20a%20couple%20of%20strangers%20to%20read%20you%20a%20carefully%20lawyered%20statement%20over%20Zoom.%20Or%20even%20worse%2C%20they%20send%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employees-fight-back-layoffs-just-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emass%20email%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%20link%20to%20an%20outplacement%20service%20and%20instantly%20shut%20you%20out%20of%20their%20systems%2C%20denying%20you%20the%20chance%20to%20even%20say%20goodbye%20to%20the%20colleagues%20you've%20worked%20alongside%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20watched%20Pietsch's%20video%2C%20my%20blood%20boiled.%20I%20felt%20the%20range%20of%20conflicting%20emotions%20that%20the%20millions%20of%20Americans%20who%20lose%20their%20jobs%20every%20year%20go%20through%3A%20baffled%2C%20angry%2C%20ashamed.%20Out%20of%20everything%20that%20happens%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%20nothing%20underscores%20the%20harshly%20transactional%20nature%20of%20employment%20more%20than%20the%20way%20companies%20terminate%20their%20employees.%20In%20the%20moment%20of%20being%20dismissed%2C%20it%20becomes%20shockingly%20clear%20that%20to%20many%20employers%2C%20their%20employees%20aren't%20people%20deserving%20of%20respect%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20just%20fungible%20commodities%20in%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20are%20times%20when%20layoffs%20are%20necessary%20for%20the%20health%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20survival%20%E2%80%94%20of%20a%20company.%20Recessions%20shatter%20the%20economy%2C%20competitors%20get%20the%20upper%20hand%2C%20new%20technology%20disrupts%20entire%20industries.%20And%20when%20layoffs%20or%20firings%20do%20happen%2C%20companies%20face%20a%20host%20of%20legal%20and%20security%20issues%20that%20have%20to%20be%20taken%20into%20consideration.%20A%20disgruntled%20employee%20might%20try%20to%20steal%20a%20list%20of%20clients%2C%20say%2C%20or%20an%20emotional%20middle%20manager%20might%20say%20something%20in%20a%20termination%20call%20that%20exposes%20the%20company%20to%20a%20lawsuit.%20Even%20when%20terminations%20are%20carried%20out%20with%20care%20and%20respect%2C%20they%20are%20inevitably%20accompanied%20by%20pain%20and%20grief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20cuts%20are%20sometimes%20unavoidable%20doesn't%20mean%20we%20have%20to%20handle%20them%20with%20all%20the%20sensitivity%20of%20a%20Mafia%20hit%20job.%20The%20current%20process%20of%20frog-marching%20employees%20out%20the%20door%20and%20disappearing%20them%20on%20Slack%20is%20not%20only%20degrading%20to%20employees%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20counterproductive%20for%20employers.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20something's%20a%20%3Cem%3Ecommon%3C%2Fem%3E%20practice%20doesn't%20make%20it%20a%20%3Cem%3Egood%3C%2Fem%3E%20practice%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sandra%20Sucher%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20practice%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School.%20%26quot%3BCompanies%20are%20kidding%20themselves%20if%20they%20think%20this%20process%20doesn't%20redound%20back%20into%20the%20organization's%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20pitiless%20and%20coldhearted%20way%20businesses%20handle%20dismissals%20isn't%20just%20destructive%20to%20those%20who%20get%20dismissed.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20harm%20comes%20to%20companies%2C%26quot%3B%20Sucher%20says.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20it's%20destructive%20to%20the%20people%20who%20remain%20behind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20destructive%3F%20To%20find%20out%2C%20I%20asked%20Culture%20Amp%2C%20which%20makes%20software%20for%20companies%20to%20track%20employee%20engagement%2C%20to%20take%20a%20look%20at%20their%20data.%20Among%20its%20clients%20that%20conducted%20layoffs%20since%20the%20pandemic%20%E2%80%94%20a%20period%20we%20may%20look%20back%20on%20as%20an%20era%20of%20peak%20callousness%20%E2%80%94%20engagement%20among%20employees%20plummeted%20the%20minute%20the%20ax%20fell.%20Even%20more%20remarkable%2C%20the%20demoralization%20and%20distrust%20among%20the%20survivors%20got%20%3Cem%3Eworse%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20the%20months%20wore%20on.%20And%20as%20decades%20of%20studies%20in%20organizational%20psychology%20have%20shown%2C%20employee%20dissatisfaction%20leads%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20costly%20problems%2C%20including%20low%20productivity%20and%20high%20turnover.%20Layoffs%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20way%20to%20boost%20the%20bottom%20line.%20But%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20they%20actually%20wind%20up%20being%20bad%20for%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20there%20a%20better%20way%20to%20handle%20layoffs%3F%20The%20answer%20is%20an%20unequivocal%20%3Cem%3Eyes.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20first%20rule%20a%20company%20should%20remember%20when%20it%20faces%20an%20imperative%20to%20slash%20costs%20is%3A%20Do%20everything%20possible%20to%20avoid%20laying%20people%20off%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECan%20the%20company%20pare%20down%20inventories%3F%20What%20about%20moving%20data%20centers%20to%20a%20cheaper%20location%3F%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20host%20of%20stuff%20that%20costs%20money%20that%20doesn't%20involve%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Sucher%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20care%20about%20your%20people%2C%20you%20start%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20isn't%20enough%2C%20employers%20can%20cut%20other%20line%20items%3A%20travel%2C%20catering%2C%20executive%20bonuses.%20They%20can%20suspend%20401(k)%20contributions.%20They%20can%20institute%20a%20hiring%20freeze%20to%20cut%20labor%20costs%20via%20attrition%2C%20and%20offer%20one-year%20unpaid%20sabbaticals%20or%20voluntary%20buyouts%2C%20enabling%20employees%20to%20maintain%20a%20sense%20of%20control%20over%20their%20own%20fates.%20If%20still%20more%20savings%20are%20needed%2C%20employers%20can%20even%20implement%20a%20temporary%2C%20across-the-board%20wage%20cut%20%E2%80%94%20demonstrating%20to%20employees%20that%20the%20company%20will%20take%20every%20measure%20possible%20to%20protect%20people's%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELayoffs%2C%20in%20short%2C%20should%20be%20the%20very%20last%20resort%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20many%20CEOs%20are%20accustomed%20to%20treating%20them%20as%20a%20go-to%20move.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20surprised%20that%20you%20can%20do%20something%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20Sucher%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20just%20doesn't%20occur%20to%20them%20that%20there's%20a%20different%20approach.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20layoffs%20are%20still%20necessary%20after%20all%20of%20that%3F%20For%20a%20few%20tips%2C%20I%20called%20Ashley%20Herd%2C%20who%20spent%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20as%20a%20corporate%20lawyer%20and%20HR%20executive%20before%20starting%20her%20own%20manager-training%20business.%20For%20starters%2C%20Herd%20says%2C%20managers%20should%20look%20the%20employees%20they're%20dismissing%20in%20the%20eye%2C%20rather%20than%20reading%20from%20a%20script.%20They%20should%20be%20prepared%20to%20stay%20on%20the%20call%20for%20as%20long%20as%20necessary%2C%20instead%20of%20rushing%20off%20to%20do%20the%20next%20one.%20And%20more%20than%20anything%2C%20they%20should%20remember%20that%20the%20employees%20whose%20jobs%20they're%20taking%20are%20human%20beings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20want%20to%20feel%20like%20they%20matter%20just%20at%20a%20basic%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20Herd%20says.%20Companies%20may%20%3Cem%3Ethink%3C%2Fem%3E%20their%20hyper-sanitized%2C%20lawyered%20approach%20will%20protect%20them%20from%20reprisals%20or%20lawsuits%20from%20angry%20ex-employees.%20But%20such%20heartlessness%2C%20Herd%20has%20found%2C%20is%20often%20pushed%20on%20companies%20by%20lawyers%20who%20have%20little%20or%20no%20experience%20in%20litigation%20or%20HR.%20In%20reality%2C%20basic%20decency%20is%20actually%20the%20most%20effective%20shield%20against%20legal%20action.%20Throwing%20people%20out%20on%20their%20ear%20only%20makes%20them%20more%20likely%20to%20sue%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0while%20making%20you%20look%20worse%20to%20a%20jury.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20do%20things%20with%20a%20human%20element%2C%26quot%3B%20Herd%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Byou're%20rarely%20going%20to%20have%20to%20litigate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20companies%20have%20gotten%20it%20right.%20When%20Stripe%20laid%20off%2014%25%20of%20its%20staff%20in%202022%2C%20it%20was%20widely%20lauded%20for%20providing%20employees%20with%20at%20least%2014%20weeks%20of%20severance%2C%20giving%20them%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20chance%20to%20have%20one-on-one%20conversations%20with%20their%20managers%2C%20and%20encouraging%20them%20to%20stay%20connected%20with%20coworkers%20and%20the%20company%20by%20giving%20them%20a%20new%20email%20address%20as%20%26quot%3Balumni.%26quot%3B%20Encouraging%20ongoing%20ties%20pays%20dividends%2C%20because%20one%20day%20ex-employees%20may%20become%20valuable%20clients%20or%20consultants%2C%20or%20even%20return%20to%20the%20company%20as%20boomerangs.%20Other%20employers%2C%20including%20Twitch%20and%20Atlassian%2C%20have%20held%20off%20on%20severing%20a%20laid-off%20employee's%20access%20to%20Slack%20for%20a%20few%20hours%2C%20or%20even%20a%20few%20days%2C%20to%20give%20them%20the%20chance%20to%20say%20goodbye%20to%20their%20colleagues.%20Recently%2C%20I%20even%20heard%20of%20a%20company%20that%20allocated%20budgets%20for%20laid-off%20teams%20to%20have%20a%20final%20meal%20together%20before%20they%20went%20their%20separate%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Nokia%20announced%20a%20restructuring%20involving%2018%2C000%20employees%20in%202011%2C%20it%20helped%20workers%20transfer%20to%20new%20parts%20of%20the%20company%20or%20get%20jobs%20elsewhere.%20It%20paid%20for%20trade-school%20programs%20if%20an%20employee%20wanted%20to%20learn%20a%20new%20skill%2C%20and%20even%20offered%20funding%20to%20those%20who%20wanted%20to%20start%20their%20own%20business.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Sucher%20says%2C%20employee%20engagement%20at%20Nokia%20remained%20steady%20throughout%20the%20restructuring%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20its%20products%20never%20suffered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExamples%20like%20Nokia%20and%20Stripe%20serve%20as%20reminders%20that%20it's%20possible%20to%20replace%20a%20shitty%20process%20with%20a%20better%20one.%20Our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employees-fight-back-layoffs-just-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecurrent%20approach%20to%20layoffs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20stems%20from%20the%20Reagan%20era%2C%20a%20period%20that%20wasn't%20exactly%20known%20for%20compassionate%20or%20innovative%20management.%20As%20work%20became%20more%20automated%2C%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20view%20employees%20as%20just%20another%20kind%20of%20robot%2C%20rather%20than%20as%20people%20with%20feelings%20and%20needs%20and%20families%20to%20support.%20Nowhere%20is%20that%20attitude%20clearer%20than%20in%20the%20way%20Cloudflare%20let%20Brittany%20Pietsch%20go.%20It's%20a%20terrible%20video%20to%20watch%2C%20because%20we%20all%20know%20we%20deserve%20better%20from%20our%20bosses%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20cathartic%20to%20hear%20someone%20say%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20voiced%20what%20it%20feels%20like%20to%20be%20the%20person%20at%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20call%2C%26quot%3B%20Sucher%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20commend%20her%2C%20because%20it's%20so%20hard%20otherwise%20to%20communicate%20to%20people%20what%20those%20moments%20are%20actually%20like.%20Hopefully%20this%20will%20cause%20people%20to%20think%20again.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708424821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b176e843bb77284ba054c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Frog-marching%20employees%20out%20the%20door%20and%20disappeari