%2C%20recruiters%20may%20find%20many%20highly%20qualified%20candidates%20among%20the%20first%20few%20applications%20they%20review!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-to-apply-for-a-job-to-get-hired-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly%20applicant%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20ideally%20within%20the%20first%2024%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20can%20maximize%20your%20chances%20of%20getting%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20able%20to%20get%20a%20referral%20or%20have%20someone%20at%20the%20company%20who%20can%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20hiring%20manager%20on%20your%20behalf%2C%20this%20can%20also%20help%20accelerate%20the%20review%20of%20your%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Reach%20out%20to%20the%20hiring%20team%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20job%20posting%20shows%20the%20recruiter%20or%20hiring%20manager%2C%20consider%20sending%20a%20message%20on%20LinkedIn.%20If%20it%20doesn't%2C%20a%20search%20of%20the%20company's%20LinkedIn%20page%20can%20help%20you%20identify%20a%20few%20people%20who%20could%20be%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReiterate%20your%20enthusiasm%20about%20the%20role%2C%20highlight%20a%20couple%20of%20things%20that%20make%20you%20a%20great%20match%2C%20share%20that%20you're%20happy%20to%20answer%20any%20additional%20questions%20about%20your%20qualifications%2C%20and%20let%20them%20know%20you%20can't%20wait%20to%20hear%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20does%20this%20help%3F%20Well%2C%20when%20I%20see%20these%20messages%20from%20applicants%2C%20I%20tend%20to%20check%20their%20profile%20or%20application%2C%20and%20if%20it's%20a%20strong%20match%2C%20I'll%20flag%20it%20for%20the%20recruiter%20or%20hiring%20team%20to%20check%20out.%20As%20noted%20above%2C%20given%20the%20high%20application%20volume%2C%20this%20can%20help%20bring%20attention%20to%20an%20application%20that%20might%20otherwise%20be%20missed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20note%3A%20don't%20be%20disappointed%20if%20you%20don't%20hear%20back%20%E2%80%94%20not%20everyone%20checks%20their%20InMail%2C%20and%20it's%20easy%20to%20miss%20these%20messages.%20But%20it's%20a%20quick%20and%20easy%20way%20that%20can%20help%20get%20eyes%20on%20your%20application%20more%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Sell%20yourself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20next%20one%20takes%20a%20bit%20of%20extra%20work%2C%20but%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20candidates%20do%20things%20like%20this%2C%20so%20it%20really%20stands%20out.%20Consider%20creating%20any%20of%20these%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EA%20short%20video%20introducing%20yourself%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EA%20deck%20where%20you%20outline%20some%20of%20your%20experience%20that%20makes%20you%20a%20strong%20match%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EA%20small%20portfolio%20of%20your%20work%20and%20linking%20this%20on%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20in%20your%20networking%20messages%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20sorts%20of%20things%20that%20are%20standard%20in%20some%20fields%20(like%20design%20or%20writing)%2C%20but%20people%20in%20most%20fields%20don't%20share%20artifacts%20that%20bring%20their%20work%20to%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreating%20something%20like%20this%20can%20really%20help%20you%20stand%20out.%20It%20shows%20what%20you%20can%20do%20for%20a%20company%2C%20and%20it's%20particularly%20helpful%20if%20you're%20a%20career%20changer%20who%20wants%20to%20show%20that%20your%20previous%20experiences%20will%20translate%20to%20a%20new%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESending%20thank%20you%20notes%20or%20following%20up%20with%20a%20work%20sample%20that%20brings%20to%20life%20something%20that%20was%20discussed%20in%20the%20interview%20are%20other%20steps%20most%20candidates%20skip%20that%20can%20leave%20a%20positive%20impression%20on%20the%20hiring%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Project%20confidence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20job%20seekers%20feel%20really%20defeated%20right%20now%2C%20and%20that%20can%20translate%20into%20how%20you%20present%20yourself%20in%20interviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20tons%20of%20psychological%20research%20that%20shows%20that%20if%20you%20speak%20with%20confidence%2C%20it%20will%20inspire%20greater%20confidence%20from%20the%20team%20about%20your%20ability%20to%20do%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20be%20afraid%20to%20speak%20like%20you're%20moving%20forward%20in%20the%20process%2C%20or%20that%20the%20job%20is%20yours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECast%20a%20vision%20for%20what%20you%20plan%20to%20do%20in%20your%20first%20few%20months%20in%20the%20role.%20Following%20an%20interview%2C%20don't%20be%20afraid%20to%20follow%20up%20with%20the%20hiring%20manager%20to%20share%20takeaways%20or%20additional%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20reinforces%20that%20you%20really%20want%20the%20role%20and%20can%20bring%20a%20lot%20to%20the%20team.%20And%20because%20very%20few%20candidates%20take%20these%20steps%2C%20it%20really%20helps%20you%20stand%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20job%20seekers%2C%20taking%20steps%20that%20can%20feel%20%26quot%3Bextra%26quot%3B%20can%20be%20daunting%2C%20especially%20when%20you're%20applying%20to%20so%20many%20roles.%20But%20I%20also%20think%20going%20%26quot%3Ball%20in%26quot%3B%20on%20a%20small%20number%20of%20roles%20that%20you're%20really%20well%20qualified%20for%20can%20ultimately%20result%20in%20needing%20far%20fewer%20applications%20to%20land%20an%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBonnie%20Dilber%20is%20the%20business%20recruiting%20team%20lead%20at%20Zapier.%20Before%20moving%20into%20tech%2C%20she%20spent%20years%20in%20education%20and%20nonprofits%20as%20a%20teacher%2C%20program%20manager%2C%20and%20recruitment%20leader.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-stand-out-candidates-applicants-job-market-recruiter-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publish