0and%2054.9%25%20in%202020-21.%20It%20was%2049.8%25%20in%202017-18%20and%2050.2%25%20in%202018-19.%20The%20WPR%20for%20persons%20of%20ages%2015%20years%20and%20above%20increased%20to%2056%25%20in%202022-23%20from%2052.9%25%20in%202021-22%20and%2052.6%25%20in%202020-21.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20LFPR%20and%20WPR%20for%20only%20the%20Muslim%20community%20has%20fallen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Muslims%2C%20the%20LFPR%20stood%20at%20around%2035.5%25%20in%202020-21%20and%2035.1%25%20in%202021-22.%20It%20declined%20to%2032.5%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20this%20data%20point%2C%20Santosh%20Mehrotra%2C%20professor%20of%20economics%2C%20Centre%20for%20Informal%20Sector%20and%20Labour%20Studies%2C%20School%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20had%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CMuslims%20have%20a%20higher%20share%20in%20the%20urban%20population%20than%20their%20share%20in%20the%20rural%20population.%20%5BThis%20is%5D%20because%20most%20Muslims%20live%20in%20urban%20areas.%20So%2C%20when%20the%20labour%20market%20revived%20in%20the%20first%20post-COVID%20year%2C%20unfortunately%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%202%20percentage%20point%20decline%20in%20the%20WPR%20of%20Muslims.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BNote%20that%5D%20WPR%20tracks%20the%20LFPR%E2%80%A6As%20the%20labour%20market%20revived%2C%20this%20is%20clear%20evidence%20that%20the%20Muslims%20have%20taken%20the%20brunt%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20a%20larger%20number%20of%20individuals%20are%20engaged%20in%20self-employment%20than%20those%20in%20casual%20labour%20and%20the%20regular%20salaried%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708414204000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20121210%2Fimage-1842.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Freligious-minority-groups-saw-greater-decline-i