-calcutta-hc-allows-bjp-leader-suvendu-adhikari-to-visit-sandeshkhali-today%2Farticleshow%2F107843385.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Calcutta%20High%20Court%20allowed%20State%20Opposition%20Leader%20Suvendu%20Adhikari%20to%20visit%20Sandeshkhali%20alone%2C%20denying%20permission%20for%20his%20supporters%20to%20accompany%20him.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20CITY%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fkolkata%2Fsetback-to-ruling-tmc-calcutta-hc-allows-bjp-leader-suvendu-adhikari-to-visit-sandeshkhali-today%2Farticleshow%2F107843385.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Modi%20Show%3A%20With%20a%20Key%20Change%2C%20BJP's%20Last%20Claim%20to%20Internal%20Democracy%20Is%20Gone%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20121245%2FUntitled-design-1-3-e1708412073428.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20filmiest%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98internal%20democracy%E2%80%99%20fig%20leaf%20now%20stands%20dropped.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20was%20left%20to%20the%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20to%20inform%20us%20that%20the%20ruling%20party%20had%2C%20in%20its%20national%20convention%20of%20the%20weekend%2C%20amended%20its%20constitution%20to%20do%20away%20with%20the%20elaborate%20farce%20of%20an%20internal%20election%20to%20select%20its%20president.%20As%20per%20the%20amendment%2C%20it%20is%20now%20for%20its%20Parliamentary%20Board%20to%20%E2%80%9Cto%20take%20a%20decision%20related%20to%20its%20president%2C%20including%20his%20or%20her%20term%20and%20its%20extension%20in%20%E2%80%99emergency%E2%80%99%20situations.%20No%20one%20knows%20whether%20there%20was%20any%20discussion%20or%20debate%20over%20this%20very%20consequential%20amendment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F04%2F04192003%2Fstatecraft.png%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-237577%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22233%5C%22%3EIn%20this%20age%20of%20shoddy%20political%20journalism%2C%20the%20reporters%20who%20otherwise%20authoritatively%20propound%20on%20this%20or%20that%20nuance%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-Amit%20Shah%20machinations%20failed%20to%20decode%20the%20amendment%20move.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20PTI%20also%20added%2C%20rather%20enigmatically%2C%20%E2%80%9CThough%20the%20party%20has%20not%20elaborated%20on%20the%20details%20and%20rationale%20behind%20the%20amendment%2C%20sources%20said%20it%20may%20have%20to%20do%20with%20the%20future%20appointments%20of%20its%20presidents.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20penny%20has%20dropped.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20its%20re-launch%20in%201980%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20always%20patted%20itself%20on%20the%20back%20as%20a%20political%20formation%20that%20was%20a%20total%20contrast%20in%20its%20internal%20functioning%20to%20that%20of%20the%20Congress%20party.%20In%20sloganeering%20short-hand%2C%20the%20BJP%20shamed%20the%20Congress%20as%20a%20party%20in%20the%20iron%20grip%20of%20a%20family%20and%20a%20party%20that%20had%20abandoned%20principles%20of%20internal%20democracy.%20The%20BJP%20leaders%20and%20apologists%20pointed%20out%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdemocratic%E2%80%9D%20selection%20process%20by%20which%20its%20presidents%20were%20%E2%80%9Celected.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20claim%20was%20a%20bit%20thick%3B%20the%20party%20has%20not%20ever%20seen%20a%20contest%20for%20its%20top%20post%2C%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20the%20Congress%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20first%20in%201997%20and%20then%20in%202023%2C%20genuine%20elections.%20The%20BJP%20presidents%20have%20always%20been%20%E2%80%9Cunanimously%E2%80%9D%20elected%3B%20the%20party%20bosses%20and%20the%20Nagpur%20commissars%20see%20to%20it%20that%20no%20one%20dares%20enter%20the%20presidential%20fray%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Cchosen%E2%80%9D%20nominee.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETill%202014%2C%20it%20was%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20that%20dictated%20the%20choice%20of%20the%20BJP%20president%3B%20and%2C%20as%20a%20corollary%2C%20the%20Nagpur%20commissars%20could%20also%20force%20an%20incumbent%20present%20to%20stand%20down.%20The%20most%20blatant%20use%20of%20this%20%E2%80%98veto%E2%80%99%20power%20was%20on%20display%20when%20L.K.%20Advani%20was%20unceremoniously%20defrocked%20after%20he%20made%20his%20discovery%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fadvani-salutes-secular-jinnah%2Fcid%2F873488%5C%22%3EM.A.%20Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20secular%20credentials%20in%202005%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20total%20mystery%20still%20surrounds%20how%20Nitin%20Gadkari%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2FPolitics%2FlnHCZ90VLlJAnMTF61ltHN%2FGadkari-out-of-race-for-BJP-president-Rajnath-seen-as-front.html%5C%22%3Ewas%20overnight%20made%20to%20step%20down%20as%20the%20party%20president%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20make%20way%20for%20Rajnath%20Singh%20in%202013.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Yet%20the%20BJP%20narrative%20continues%20to%20harp%20on%20its%20%E2%80%98democratic%E2%80%99%20internal%20arrangements.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20fiction%20may%20be%20hard%20to%20maintain%20after%20the%20recent%20amendment.%20Since%202014%2C%20when%20Narendra%20Modi%20emerged%20as%20the%20most%20effective%20vote-getter%20for%20the%20BJP%2C%20it%20is%20he%20who%20has%20claimed%20a%20right%20to%20re-arrange%20the%20leadership%20line-up.%20When%20veterans%20like%20Advani%20and%20Murli%20Manohar%20Joshi%20were%20kicked%20upstairs%20to%20some%20kind%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Emargdarshak%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Emandal%20%3C%2Fem%3E(literally%2C%20group%20which%20points%20one%20to%20the%20right%20path)%E2%80%99%2C%C2%A0it%20was%20a%20most%20hostile%20takeover%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20with%20the%20commissars%20from%20Nagpur%20being%20reduced%20to%20silent%20spectators.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Modification%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20BJP%20was%20complete%20and%20total%20when%20Amit%20Shah%20was%20%E2%80%98elected%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20of%20course%2C%20unopposed%20%E2%80%93%20in%202014.%20The%20BJP%20was%20imitating%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20model%3A%20since%20she%20was%20seen%20as%20the%20one%20and%20only%20vote-getter%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%20it%20was%20only%20natural%20that%20the%20party%20should%20be%20at%20her%20beck%20and%20call%2C%20though%20she%20was%20careful%20to%20go%20through%20the%20formal%20process%20of%20internal%20consultation%20in%20the%20Congress%20Parliamentary%20Board.%20Every%20taluka%20Congress%20leader%20knew%20that%20it%20was%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20diktat%20that%20would%20govern%20party%20matters%20from%20the%20district%20level%20up.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20121849%2FGGinNtRXoAAUYbn-1024x598.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20121849%2FGGinNtRXoAAUYbn-1024x598.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20121849%2FGGinNtRXoAAUYbn-300x175.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20121849%2FGGinNtRXoAAUYbn.jpg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697923%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22491%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98%3Cspan%3EBut%20it%20is%20Modi%2C%20with%20some%20assistance%20from%20Shah%2C%20who%20decides%20who%20will%20be%20in%20the%20Parliamentary%20Board.%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fspan%3EPhoto%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202024%20BJP%20party%20constitution%20amendment%20makes%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20board%20a%20super-politburo.%20But%20it%20is%20Modi%2C%20with%20some%20assistance%20from%20Shah%2C%20who%20decides%20who%20will%20be%20in%20the%20Parliamentary%20Board.%20Whether%20it%20is%20J.P.%20Nadda%20or%20any%20other%20token%20president%2C%20the%20total%20power%20and%20compete%20control%20rests%20incontestably%20with%20Modi.%20Not%20since%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20(1984-89)%20has%20any%20single%20political%20leader%20%E2%80%93%20not%20even%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20%E2%80%93%20had%20this%20kind%20of%20absolute%20grip%20over%20the%20levers%20of%20power%20in%20the%20national%20government%20and%20the%20ruling%20party.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20just%20concluded%20national%20convention%20predictably%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20grand%20celebration%20of%20the%20Modi%20cult.%20Never%20before%20has%20this%20self-professed%20%E2%80%9Cdemocratic%E2%80%9D%20party%20put%20someone%20on%20as%20high%20a%20pedestal%20as%20the%20one%20Modi%20was%20put%20on.%20All%20other%20so-called%20senior%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20Rajnath%20Singh%2C%20J.P.%20Nadda%2C%20and%20even%20Amit%20Shah%20%E2%80%93%20were%20reduced%20to%20chorus%20boys%2C%20singing%20hymns%20to%20the%20omnipotent%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Esevak%20%3C%2Fem%3E(literally%2C%20servant)%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20harbinger%20of%20a%201%2C000%20years%20of%20Ram%20Rajya.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20those%20self-styled%20%E2%80%98moral%20guardians%E2%80%99%20in%20Nagpur%20who%20all%20these%20decades%20pretended%20to%20believe%20in%20the%20supremacy%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Corganisation%E2%80%9D%20are%20content%20to%20be%20the%20%E2%80%9Cextras%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20show.%20If%20anything%2C%20the%202024%20amendment%20is%20a%20snub%20to%20the%20RSS%20bosses.%20The%20BJP%20now%20belongs%20to%20Modi.%20Any%20pretext%20of%20consultation%2C%20consensus%20and%20internal%20democracy%20is%20just%20an%20eyewash.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0This%20deification%20of%20Modi%20is%20not%20just%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20internal%20issue.%20Its%20implications%20for%20the%20polity%20are%20obvious%20and%20odious.%20When%20a%20ruling%20party%20chooses%20to%20concentrate%20all%20power%20in%20one%20person%2C%20the%20polity%20invariably%20lurches%20towards%20an%20authoritarian%20temptation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20so-called%20%E2%80%9CModi%20guarantee%E2%80%9D%20is%20an%20in-your-face%20personality%20cult%2C%20now%20fully%20entrenched%20and%20internalised%20by%20the%20party%20as%20also%20by%20the%20bureaucracy%20and%20the%20large%20swathes%20of%20the%20media.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20democracy%20already%20stands%20pock-marked%20with%20relentless%20personalisation%20of%20every%20area%20of%20national%20life.%20The%20formal%20re-arrangement%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20can%20only%20be%20the%20proverbial%20tip%20of%20the%20authoritarian%20iceberg%20lurching%20just%20below%20the%20surface%20%E2%80%93%20a%20warning%20bell%20that%20should%20be%20heard.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHarish%20Khare%20is%20a%20former%20editor-in-chief%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Tribune.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708412440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F20121245%2FUntitled-design-1-3-e1708412073428.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-bjp-internal-democracy-amendment%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20formal%20re-arrangement%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20can%20only%20be%20the%20proverbial%20tip%20of%20the%20authoritarian%20iceberg%20lurching%20just%20below%20the%20surface.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-bjp-internal-democracy-amendment%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gaumont%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20Sabine%20de%20Mardt%20Discusses%20Timely%20Series%20%E2%80%98The%20Interpreter%20of%20Silence%2C%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%98In%20Her%20Car%2C%E2%80%99%20New%20Projects%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708412230000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FSabine-2023_DH-Shooting-1.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235916122%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Since%20its%20establishment%20in%202018%2C%20Gaumont%20Germany%20has%20produced%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20series%20and%20TV%20movies%2C%20among%20them%20such%20timely%20shows%20as%20the%20critically%20acclaimed%20%E2%80%9CDeutsches%20Haus%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9CThe%20Interpreter%20of%20Silence%E2%80%9D)%2C%20which%20was%20nominated%20for%20the%20Critics%20Choice%20Awards%2C%20and%20the%20Ukrainian%20series%20%E2%80%9CIn%20Her%20Car.%E2%80%9D%20A%20subsidiary%20of%20the%20French%20entertainment%20powerhouse%2C%20the%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Emeza805%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fgaumont-germany-sabine-de-mardt-1235916122%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fgaumont-germany-sabine-de-mardt-1235916122%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fgaumont-germany-sabine-de-mardt-1235916122%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%20Policies%20Are%20Consistent%20With%20the%20Great%20Power%20Aspirations%20of%20Its%20Elites%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22162028%2Fgaza-israel-barrier.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20simultaneous%20wars%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%2C%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20seemingly%20contradictory%20policy%20responses%20towards%20them%2C%20shine%20a%20light%20on%20the%20drivers%20of%20Indian%20power%3A%20traditional%20great%20power%20ambitions%20within%20the%20US-led%20international%20order%2C%20coupled%20with%20more%20recent%20economic%20and%20civilisational%20self-confidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20drivers%20have%20been%20more%20or%20less%20hidden%20in%20plain%20sight%20since%201947%2C%20and%20perhaps%20even%20before%20Independence%2C%20under%20a%20convenient%20veneer%20of%20anti-colonialism%2C%20non-alignment%2C%20principled%20friendship%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20(and%20later%20Russia)%20as%20well%20as%20alleged%20Nehruvian%20attachment%20to%20Soviet%20economic%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20establishment%2C%20initially%20nurtured%20under%20British%20colonial%20rule%20and%20only%20periodically%20and%20pragmatically%20modified%20since%2C%20has%20helped%20craft%20a%20self-serving%20myth%20of%20post-colonial%20idealism%2C%20non-alignment%2C%20and%20third%20worldism%2FGlobal%20South(ism)%2C%20while%20all%20the%20while%20remaining%20well%20within%20the%20mindsets%2C%20relationships%2C%20and%20opportunities%20afforded%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FIndia-America-Relations-1942-62-Rooted-in-the-Liberal-International-Order%2FBhardwaj%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032094281%5C%22%3EAnglo-American%20liberal%20international%20system%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20India%E2%80%99s%20power%20elite%20continues%20successfully%20to%20pull%20off%20this%20smoke-and-mirrors%20strategy%20is%20quite%20remarkable%20but%20it%20could%20not%20do%20it%20alone.%20The%20image%20is%20also%20projected%20by%20other%20liberal%20international%20order%20powers%20to%20help%20maintain%20the%20myth%20because%20it%20has%20served%20them%20well%20to%20have%20India%20seen%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20no%20eternal%20allies%E2%80%A6Our%20interests%20are%20eternal%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20the%20seemingly%20contradictory%20policies%20towards%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%20are%20consistent%20if%20a%20bird%E2%80%99s%20eye%20lens%20is%20taken.%20There%20are%20pragmatic%20and%20historical%20reasons%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20stance%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20aggression%20in%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%93%20going%20back%20to%20the%201950s%2C%20as%20we%20explain%20below.%20And%20there%20are%20reasons%20why%20the%20United%20States%2C%20which%20is%20officially%20unhappy%20with%20India%E2%80%99s%20stance%2C%20continues%20to%20engage%20ever%20more%20deeply%20with%20the%20emerging%20great%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20geopolitical%20location%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20so-called%20Indo-Pacific%20%E2%80%93%20is%20a%20key%20factor%20in%20US%20calculations%20and%20cautious%20language%20towards%20India.%20And%20reasons%20rooted%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20power%20politics%20and%20geo-economics%20explain%20why%20the%20above%20stance%20is%20consistent%20with%20its%20Israel-Gaza%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20there%20are%20those%20who%20argue%20that%20India%20is%20driven%20by%20its%20position%20as%20a%20leader%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20as%20a%20postcolonial%20state%2C%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20BRICS%2B%20that%E2%80%99s%20challenging%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cairn.info%2Frevue-politique-etrangere-2008-5-page-65.htm%5C%22%3EUS-led%20liberal%20order%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yet%20others%20suggest%20that%20India%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3EUS%20satellite%3C%2Fem%3E%20especially%20in%20its%20attitudes%20towards%20China%2C%20and%20its%20membership%20in%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20multilateral%20groupings%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region%20that%20exclude%20and%20seek%20to%20%E2%80%98contain%E2%80%99%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsws.org%2Fen%2Farticles%2F2024%2F02%2F12%2Fheyc-f12.html%5C%22%3Esubordinate%20China%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20more%20complex%20and%20reveals%20a%20sophisticated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2FIndian-Service-Foreign-Policy-1923-1961-ebook%2Fdp%2FB08MVFM3QS%5C%22%3Eforeign%20policy%20establishment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20embedded%20in%20a%20thin%20layer%20of%20politically-expedient%20feel-good%20idealistic%20post-colonialism%20that%20veils%20an%20iron-fisted%20pragmatic%20great%20power%20in%20the%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20British%20foreign%20secretary%20Lord%20Palmerston%20said%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20in%201848%2C%20applies%20to%20India%20today%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20no%20eternal%20allies%2C%20and%20we%20have%20no%20perpetual%20enemies.%20Our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1991%2F02%2F07%2Fopinion%2Fessay-friends-more-than-interests.html%5C%22%3Einterests%20are%20eternal%20and%20perpetual%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20those%20interests%20it%20is%20our%20duty%20to%20follow.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fflashpoints-in-ukraine-gaza-yemen-and-taiwan-point-to-a-global-war-in-the-making%5C%22%3EFlashpoints%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Gaza%2C%20Yemen%20and%20Taiwan%20Point%20to%20a%20Global%20War%20in%20the%20Making%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20supports%20normalisation%20with%20Israel%2C%20de-hyphenation%20of%20Israel-Palestine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20catastrophic%20war%20in%20Gaza%20%E2%80%93%20in%20regard%20to%20which%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20has%20ordered%20Israel%20to%20refrain%20from%20and%20prevent%20genocide%20%E2%80%93%20India%20condemned%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20attacks%20of%20October%207%2C%202023%2C%20then%20refused%2C%20for%20three%20months%2C%20to%20support%20a%20ceasefire%20resolution%20at%20the%20UN%2C%20and%20has%20since%20called%20for%20a%20two%20state%20solution%20in%20general%20terms.%20This%20is%20for%20pragmatic%20reasons%20of%20power%20politics%20including%20a%20long-term%20shift%20towards%20delicate%20bilateral%20relationship%20building%20across%20the%20region%2C%20including%20Israel%2C%20Arab%20states%2C%20and%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestine%20has%20been%20compartmentalised%20and%20relegated%2C%20in%20service%20of%20Indian%20elite%20interests%2C%20%E2%80%9Cde-hyphenated%E2%80%9D%2C%20separated%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20Israel.%20As%20an%20MEA%20spokesperson%20noted%20in%20January%20in%20response%20to%20a%20question%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20position%20on%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20genocide%20charge%20against%20Israel%20at%20the%20ICJ%3A%20%E2%80%9COur%20position%20on%20the%20conflict%2C%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20conflict%20is%E2%80%A6%20it%20has%20been%20consistent%20and%20steadfast.%20We%20have%20condemned%20terrorism%2C%20we%20have%20called%20for%20release%20of%20hostages%2C%20we%20have%20sought%20protection%20of%20civilians%20and%E2%80%A6%20we%20have%20called%20for%20provision%20of%20humanitarian%20assistance%20and%20of%20course%20we%20stand%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2Fmedia-briefings.htm%3Fdtl%2F37518%2Ftranscript%2Bof%2Bweekly%2Bmedia%2Bbriefing%2Bby%2Bthe%2Bofficial%2Bspokesperson%2Bjanuary%2B18%2B2024%5C%22%3Elong-term%20two-state%20solution%3C%2Fa%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYet%2C%20convenient%20mythologies%20persist%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20enduring%20perception%20in%20strategic%20circles%20that%20PM%20Narendra%20Modi%20has%20riled%20America%2C%20its%20close%20strategic%20partner%2C%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%2C%20by%20refusing%20to%20unreservedly%20condemn%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20failing%20to%20call%20the%20Kremlin%20an%20aggressor.%20New%20Delhi%20also%20abstained%20from%20voting%20against%20Russia%20in%20the%20UN%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpminewyork.gov.in%2Fstatementsearch%3Fid%3DeyJpdiI6IjRyT01pd3pyVHBQalhXNW5WVEY3aHc9PSIsInZhbHVlIjoiSzdnaFwvS3M4bFpBXC9aSW93SXQrVGFRPT0iLCJtYWMiOiIyNTRiOTFjNTY5YmFjZmNhMzZiNWM2Mzk0M2FhYmU1ZDQ5YWQ1ZmY5NDk5ZjM1ODkxNWRiZTU2NTNiOTk3MmEwIn0%3D%5C%22%3ESecurity%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2022%2F04%2F1115782%5C%22%3EGeneral%20Assembly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Findia-abstains-in-unhrc-vote-on-establishing-independent-commission-of-inquiry-on-russia-ukraine-crisis%2Farticle65190155.ece%5C%22%3EHuman%20Rights%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20has%20openly%20defied%20western%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%20by%20indulging%20in%20opportunistic%20purchases%20of%20cheap%20Russian%20oil.%20In%202023%2C%20India%20was%20the%20largest%20buyer%20of%20Russian%20seaborne%20crude%2C%20accounting%20for%2038%25%20of%20these%20exports.%20Many%20commentators%20have%20been%20unduly%20perturbed%20about%20India%20inconsistency%20in%20supporting%20the%20so-called%20rule-based%20order%20especially%20when%20the%20trans-Atlantic%20powers%20are%20focused%20on%20making%20Russia%20capitulate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Modi%20has%20not%20been%20as%20brazen%20as%20the%20Hungarian%20Prime%20Minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-12-21%2Forban-questions-if-russia-s-invasion-of-ukraine-is-a-war%5C%22%3EViktor%20Mih%C3%A1ly%20Orban%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20has%20called%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%9Ca%20military%20operation%E2%80%9D%20and%20not%20war.%20India%20has%20provided%20tacit%20support%20to%20Putin%20simultaneously%20reiterating%20conventional%20diplomatic%20wisdoms%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Findia-stands-for-respecting-sovereignty-adherence-to-international-law-pm-on-chinas-maritime-assertiveness%2Farticle66874780.ece%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98upholding%20international%20law%20and%20national%20sovereignty%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20pushing%20for%20a%20pragmatic%20and%20permanent%20solution%20to%20the%20conflict.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20those%20who%20were%20hoping%20that%20New%20Delhi%2C%20because%20of%20its%20alignment%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20would%20declare%20the%20Kremlin%20a%20geo-political%20burden%20are%20disappointed.%20The%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20instead%20of%20accelerating%20has%20retarded%20the%20decline%20in%20India-Russia%20relationship.%20India%20stood%20with%20Russia%20for%20both%20strategic%20as%20well%20as%20pragmatic%20reasons.%20Since%20the%20mid-1950s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2023%2F05%2Fwhy-did-china-and-india-support-a-un-resolution-acknowledging-russian-aggression-against-ukraine%2F%5C%22%3ERussia%20has%20vetoed%3C%2Fa%3E%20every%20move%20by%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20in%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20to%20browbeat%20India%20on%20the%20Kashmir%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20mid-1960s%2C%20Russia%20supported%20India%E2%80%99s%20defence%20needs.%20It%20mediated%20peace%20at%20the%20end%20of%20Indo-Pakistan%20war%20of%201965.%20In%20the%201971%20Bangladesh%20war%2C%20Moscow%20again%20helped%20New%20Delhi%20ward%20off%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20a%20US%20Navy%20carrier%20battle%20group%20in%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndo-Russian%20nuclear%20cooperation%20has%20been%20the%20lynchpin%20of%20the%20bilateral%20ties.%20It%20is%20thanks%20to%20decades%20of%20India-Russia%20naval%20engagement%20that%20today%20India%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20countries%20in%20Asia%20that%20can%20build%20a%20nuclear%20submarine.%20Russia%20may%20have%20joined%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20in%20condemning%20India%20for%20its%201998%20nuclear%20tests%20but%20it%20refused%20to%20impose%20sanctions%20on%20India%2C%20unlike%20the%20US%2C%20Japan%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotwithstanding%20the%20criticism%20levelled%20against%20India%20in%20the%20western%20media%2C%20the%20US%20State%20Department%2C%20more%20concerned%20with%20India%20as%20a%20counterpoise%20to%20China%2C%20has%20been%20accommodative%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20reluctance%20to%20decouple%20from%20Russia.%20In%20July%20last%20year%2C%20the%20US%20Congress%20approved%20a%20waiver%20to%20India%20against%20the%20punitive%20Countering%20America%E2%80%99s%20Adversaries%20Through%20Sanctions%20Act%3Cem%3E%20(%3C%2Fem%3ECAATSA)%20sanctions%20for%20its%20purchase%20of%20the%20S-400%20missile%20defence%20system%20from%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECAATSA%20authorises%20the%20US%20administration%20to%20impose%20sanctions%20on%20countries%20that%20purchase%20major%20defence%20hardware%20from%20Russia.%20These%20sanctions%20had%20come%20into%20force%20in%20response%20to%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20in%202014%20and%20its%20alleged%20meddling%20in%20the%202016%20US%20presidential%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThings%20are%20not%20always%20what%20they%20seem%20in%20international%20relations.%20It%20is%20not%20always%20necessary%20for%20partners%20and%20allies%20to%20converge%20on%20every%20issue.%20In%20the%20conduct%20of%20international%20relations%2C%20short-term%20tactical%20divergences%20between%20partners%20and%20allies%20may%20be%20necessary%20for%20larger%20strategic%20convergence.%20We%20must%20consider%20the%20deeper%20tides%20rather%20than%20surface%20ripples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20very%20special%20double%20act%20shows%20how%20it%20works%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELook%20at%20post-war%20Anglo-American%20relations.%20The%20former%20colonial%20power%20recognised%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2020%2Fjan%2F07%2Fbritain-recognises-communist-government-of-china-1950%5C%22%3Ecommunist%20regime%20in%20China%20in%201950%20while%20the%20latter%20was%20completely%20opposed%20to%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20entry%20in%20the%20United%20Nations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F26925945%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20mid-1950s%20when%20the%20US%20started%20poking%20China%20in%20Tibet%20and%20Taiwan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20London%20was%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20trading%20partner.%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20subtle%20pro-China%20stance%20was%20not%20necessarily%20antithetical%20to%20America%E2%80%99s%20larger%20strategic%20needs%20to%20woo%20China%20away%20from%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20while%20the%20policy%20also%20helped%20it%20to%20protect%20its%20territorial%20possessions%20within%20China.%20Britain%20could%20take%20a%20divergent%20stand%20partly%20because%20China%20was%20not%20America%E2%80%99s%20peer%20competitor%20at%20that%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20engagement%20with%20Russia%20cannot%20be%20viewed%20as%20completely%20selfish.%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20with%20Moscow%20is%20essential%20for%20America%20too%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20woo%20Russia%20back%20into%20the%20western%20camp%20and%20split%20the%20Sino-Russian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Fchina%2Flimits-of-a-no-limits-partnership-china-russia%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cno-limits%20partnership%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Washington%20is%20unlikely%20to%20permit%20similar%20engagement%20by%20New%20Delhi%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20where%20China%2C%20its%20peer%20competitor%2C%20is%20to%20be%20tamed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDifferent%20region%2C%20same%20principles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20stance%20on%20Israeli%20military%20action%20and%20large-scale%20killing%20of%20Palestinians%20has%20been%20equally%20criticised%20by%20many%20used%20to%20seeing%20India%20take%20an%20unequivocal%20stand%20in%20favour%20of%20Palestinians.%20Although%20India%20has%20issued%20politically%20correct%20statements%20in%20support%20of%20a%20two-state%20solution%20for%20resolution%20of%20the%20long-standing%20Israel-Palestine%20conflict%2C%20its%20heart%20is%20with%20the%20Israeli%20state%20and%20even%20the%20Netanyahu%20regime.%20As%20the%20Israeli%20bombing%20moved%20though%20gear%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.project-syndicate.org%2Fcommentary%2Findia-response-to-israel-hamas-war-foreign-policy-shift-away-from-nonalignment-by-shashi-tharoor-2023-11%5C%22%3ENew%20Delhi%20pointedly%20abstained%20from%20voting%20in%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20resolution%20that%20urged%20a%20humanitarian%20truce%20in%20Gaza%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20the%20resolution%20did%20not%20condemn%20the%20terror%20attacks%20of%20October%207%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20sees%20Israel%20as%20an%20important%20partner%20in%20its%20quest%20to%20indigenise%20defence%20technology%20as%20well%20as%20a%20ally%20in%20its%20competition%20for%20new%20trade%20routes%20with%20China.%20New%20Delhi%20is%20looking%20forward%20to%20the%20development%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2023%2F38%2Fcomment%2Fgeopolitics-rooted-routes.html%5C%22%3EIndia-Middle%20East-Europe%20Economic%20Corridor%20(IMEC)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20multimodal%20transportation%20corridor%20stretching%20across%20the%20Arabian%20Sea%20from%20India%20to%20Israel%20via%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20Jordan%20to%20counter%20China%E2%80%99s%20increasing%20presence%20in%20West%20Asia%20affairs.%20IMEC%20is%20backed%20by%20the%20United%20States%20(US)%20along%20with%20the%20European%20Union%20(EU)%2C%20mainly%20to%20counter%20China%E2%80%99s%20increasing%20footprint%20in%20West%20Asia%20and%20curtail%20Iranian%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20government%20has%20built%20on%20the%20India%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20strategy%20of%20transforming%20bilateral%20relations%20with%20the%20Gulf%20Cooperation%20Council%20states%2C%20Israel%20and%20Iran%20%E2%80%93%20simultaneously.%20These%20relationships%20are%20now%20more%20comprehensive%20than%20oil-related%20links%20%E2%80%93%20spanning%20investments%2C%20technology%20collaborations%20in%20food%20security%20and%20renewable%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gulf%20region%20is%20now%20the%20source%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20third-%20and%20fourth-largest%20trading%20partners%20(UAE%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20respectively)%2C%20as%20India-Israel%20trade%20volume%20exceeded%C2%A0%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indembassyisrael.gov.in%2Fpages%3Fid%3Dnel5a%26subid%3D7ax9b%5C%22%3E%2410.1%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20(excluding%20defence)%20in%202022-2023.%20India%20has%20proven%20attractive%20to%20a%20region%20seeking%20to%20diversify%20away%20from%20oil%20and%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20increasing%20convergence%20of%20strategic%20and%20economic%20interests%20between%20India%2C%20Israel%2C%20and%20the%20UAE%20led%20them%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Finternational%2Fi2u2-can-become-a-regional-feature-like-the-quad-jake-sullivan%2Farticle65637011.ece%5C%22%3Esign%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20quadrilateral%20agreement%20with%20the%20United%20States%20(US)%20known%20as%20I2U2%2C%20in%20October%202021.%20The%20focal%20point%20is%20mitigating%20global%20challenges%3A%20India%2C%20Israel%20and%20the%20UAE%20initiated%20plans%20in%202022%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mei.edu%2Fpublications%2Findia-middle-east-food-corridor-how-uae-israel-and-india-are-forging-new-inter%5C%22%3EIndia-Middle%20East%20Food%20Corridor%20%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.geopoliticalmonitor.com%2Fthe-india-middle-east-europe-corridor-challenges-ahead%2F%5C%22%3EIndia-Middle%20East-Europe%20Economic%20Corridor%20(IMEEC)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20launched%20at%20the%20September%202023%20G20%20Summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20aiming%20to%20bolster%20economic%20integration%20between%20Asia%2C%20Europe%2C%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%3B%20again%2C%20challenging%20China%E2%80%99s%20BRI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20and%20Palestine%20are%20now%20%E2%80%98de-hyphenated%E2%80%99%20in%20India%20foreign%20policy%20%E2%80%93%20compartmentalised%2C%20much%20as%20they%20are%20in%20the%20attitudes%20of%20the%20Gulf%20states%20since%20the%20inking%20of%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20in%202021.%20The%20current%20conflict%20however%20will%20likely%20have%20multiple%20effects%20%E2%80%93%20cooling%20further%20bilateral%20developments%20with%20Israel%20for%20fear%20of%20Arab%20reactions%2C%20while%20solidifying%20further%20India%20and%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20anti-terror%20cooperation.%20Rising%20tensions%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20are%20also%20driving%20increased%20maritime%20%E2%80%98security%E2%80%99%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20times%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20approaches%20may%20seem%20to%20be%20in%20divergence%20and%20defiance%20of%20the%20west.%20However%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20China%2C%20there%20is%20no%20ambiguity%20in%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20mind%20that%20its%20big%20neighbour%20is%20a%20monster%20that%20has%20to%20be%20tackled%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20United%20States%20and%20its%20allies.%20Washington%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mind%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20flirtations%20with%20Putin%20as%20long%20as%20he%20is%20willing%20to%20join%20the%20chorus%20in%20condemning%20and%20containing%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20China%20and%20its%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fbackstory-india-is-on-the-wrong-side-of-history-on-gaza-and-the-media-has-not-helped%5C%22%3EBackstory%3A%C2%A0India%20Is%20on%20the%20Wrong%20Side%20of%20History%20on%20Gaza%2C%20and%20the%20Media%20Has%20Not%20Helped%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBye%20bye%20Nehruvian%20symbolic%20idealism%2C%20hello%20India%20First%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20elements%20that%20guide%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20recent%20foreign%20policy%20choices%20are%20its%20efforts%20to%20jettison%20overt%20displays%20of%20Nehruvian%20idealism%20normally%20associated%20with%20Indian%20foreign%20policy%20and%20to%20openly%20declare%20its%20ambitions%20as%20a%20great%20power%20capable%20of%20guiding%20the%20destinies%20of%20the%20global%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ideological%20element%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20policy%20comes%20from%20its%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20First%E2%80%9D%20approach%20that%20prioritises%20national%20interests%20over%20largely%20symbolic%20expressions%20of%20morality%20in%20conduct%20of%20international%20relations.%20This%20is%20reminiscent%20of%20Donald%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20muscular%20but%20no-war%20approach.%20Therefore%2C%20under%20Prime%20Minster%20Modi%2C%20India%20may%20conduct%20%E2%80%98surgical%20strikes%E2%80%99%20but%20is%20likely%20to%20refrain%20from%20full-fledged%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20predictions%20of%20an%20emerging%20%E2%80%98Indian%20century%E2%80%99%20maybe%20somewhat%20premature%2C%20the%20ambition%20has%20been%20there%20since%20the%20creation%2C%20long%20before%20the%20current%20rebranding%20of%20India%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20140714130445%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fnews.oneindia.in%2F2007%2F12%2F01%2F21st-century-is-going-to-be-indian-century-alagappan-1196517764.html%5C%22%3Ecivilisational%20power%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Ukraine%20and%20Gaza%20war%20responses%20are%20consistent%20not%20contradictory.%20What%20conventional%20observers%20call%20hypocrisy%20should%20be%20called%20by%20its%20true%20name%3A%20self-interested%20elite%20power%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Atul%20Bhardwaj%20is%20an%20honorary%20research%20fellow%20in%20the%20department%20of%20international%20politics%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EIndia-America%20Relations%20(1942-62)%3A%20Rooted%20in%20the%20Liberal%20International%20Order%C2%A0%3Cem%3E(Routledge%2C%202018).%C2%A0%3C%2Fe